title: In vs On vs At Practice
description: Practice the difference between 'in', 'on' and 'at' with fill-in-the-blank questions.

questions.question: He left his keys ___ the table.
I like to jog ___ the evening.
The cat is sleeping ___ the sofa.
I hung the picture ___ the wall.
My office is ___ the second floor.
There is a spider ___ the ceiling.
He put his books ___ his bag.
She left the notes ___ my desk.
The picture is ___ the top of the page.
My birthday is ___ the first of May.
I'll see you ___ the bus stop.
The kids are playing ___ the yard.
There's a note ___ the bottom of the page.
The dog is sleeping ___ the floor.
She is waiting ___ the parking lot.
Let's watch a movie ___ the evening.
He is good ___ playing the guitar.
